// "Browse packs" UI on the setup screen (consensustrivia.com + gradwritetrivia.org).
//
// PACK_CATALOG is regenerated by scrape_packs.py — see CLAUDE.md. Re-run
// the scraper when consensustrivia.com adds new packs. GRADWRITE_CATALOG is
// maintained by hand (the Gradwrite site is small and rarely changes) and is
// deliberately a separate const so pasting fresh scraper output over
// PACK_CATALOG can't wipe it.
//
// consensustrivia.com serves its pack PDFs with NO CORS header, so a browser
// on the live (GitHub Pages) site can't read the bytes via a plain fetch(). We
// relay through our own Cloudflare Worker (PACK_PROXY_BASE — see
// workers/pack-proxy/) which re-emits the pack with permissive CORS.
// gradwritetrivia.org sends `Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *`, so its packs are
// fetched directly (directCors below) with the relay chain as a fallback.
//
// fetchWithFallback walks a list of attempts: direct fetch (when the source
// allows it), our Worker relay, then the free public proxies as a legacy
// fallback. If every fetch path fails (e.g. the Worker is unset or over its
// daily quota and the public proxies are down), the caller degrades to a
// plain manual-download link — see renderManualFallback.

import { escapeHtml } from '../util/escape.js';
import { looksLikePdfOrZip } from '../parser/zip.js';
import { parsePdf, processZipBuffer } from '../loader.js';

